text.section:
A person is guilty of providing fraudulent identification for the sale of metals when the person provides to any person required to keep a record of the purchase of metals pursuant to KRS 433.890:
A false name or other information required to be disclosed;
A false, fraudulent, altered, or counterfeit identification document;
A false, fraudulent, altered, or counterfeit vehicle license plate; or
A false, fraudulent, altered, or counterfeit ownership document.
